## Conclusion and Opinion

The evidence clearly indicates that stereotyping has overwhelmingly negative effects on individuals and society. It impairs cognitive performance through stereotype threat, causes lasting psychological harm, fosters social division, perpetuates systemic racism, and negatively impacts child development and mental health. While stereotyping may serve as a cognitive shortcut, the costs far outweigh any perceived benefits.

In my opinion, addressing stereotyping requires comprehensive education to raise awareness of its unconscious nature and harmful consequences. Incorporating empathy-building curricula and promoting media literacy can help reduce the prevalence and impact of stereotypes. Society must actively challenge and dismantle stereotypes to foster inclusion, equity, and psychological well-being for all members.

